5000|$|In 1812 Fabré-Palaprat {{formed the}} <b>Johannite</b> Church, {{introducing}} faith-based elements into his order. He later ordained Ferdinand-François Châtel, a radical clergyman {{who left the}} priesthood following the July Revolution, as Primate of the <b>Johannite</b> church, on 4 May 1831. Châtel established his new French Catholic Church (Eglise Catholique Française) in former shop premises in Montmartre, decorating it with the bust of Louis Philippe I placed under the Tricolour flag. The <b>Johannite</b> church was located in a former bottle shop in the Cour des miracles, dubbed the [...] "Apostolic Court of the Temple". The Order dated its documents from 'Magistropolis', a mystical calendar commencing from {{the foundation of the}} Knights Templar in 1118.|$|E
